---
description: Audits a UI screen or flow description against Nielsen's 10 usability heuristics, returning pass/fail findings.
category: Design
model: googleai/gemini-flash-latest
input:
  schema:
    screen_description: string
    user_goal: string
---
You are auditing a UI screen or flow against usability heuristics. Be specific — cite the exact element or step, not a general impression.

User's goal on this screen: {{user_goal}}
Screen/flow description: {{screen_description}}

Evaluate against each of Nielsen's 10 heuristics and output one row per heuristic in this table:

| Heuristic | Pass/Fail/Partial | Evidence | Fix |
|---|---|---|---|
| Visibility of system status | | | |
| Match with real world | | | |
| User control and freedom | | | |
| Consistency and standards | | | |
| Error prevention | | | |
| Recognition over recall | | | |
| Flexibility and efficiency | | | |
| Aesthetic and minimalist design | | | |
| Help users recognize/diagnose/recover from errors | | | |
| Help and documentation | | | |

After the table, list the top 3 fixes ranked by expected impact on the user's stated goal, not by ease of implementation.
